Box: Shocker
Difficulty: Easy
OS: Linux

Recon:
- nmap -sC -sV -p- <IP>
- Found port 80 open
- Gobuster revealed /cgi-bin/test.sh

Exploitation:
- Tested for Shellshock vulnerability with crafted User-Agent header
- Confirmed RCE
- Gained reverse shell using bash payload

Privilege Escalation:
- Enumerated sudo -l
- Found ability to run perl as root
- Escalated with perl -e 'exec "/bin/sh";'

Mitigations:
- Patch bash (Shellshock vulnerability)
- Restrict CGI usage
- Sanitize headers
